	The CIA doesn't like giving its people too much in the way of
	spy paraphenalia, it's way too incriminating.  There are a couple
	of cases in the literature that indicate that Warsaw Pact
	intell. forces used the number stations (and their successors
	probably still do.).

	Try finding:

	Uno, dos, cuatro: a guide to the number stations

	by Havana Moon (Tiare Publications) $13.95

	at your local HAM radio shop.

	Alec Chambers
